tary service, and a year as a prisoner of war in Perugia, he turned from the world and devoted himself to caring for the poor and sick. He was joined by groups of disciples, calling themselves ‘minor friars’ (<i>friari minores</i>). The main features of the Franciscan rule are humility, poverty, and love for all living creatures. The given name occurs occasionally in England as early as  1300 , and more frequently from the early 16th century, when there was a surge of admiration for, and imitation of, Italian Renaissance culture."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705193,"age":7,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Sir Francis Fogge was born in 1330, in Repton, Derbyshire, England as the son of John Fogge. He married Anne De Valoignes in 1362, in Kent, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1377, at the age of 47, and was buried in Cheriton, Kent, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1330–1377":"1330–1377","1346–Female":"1346–Surnud","1363–1422":"1363–1422","1308–Male":"1308–Surnud","1337":"1337","1346":"1346","1422":"1422","1377":"1377","1453":"1453","1330":"1330","1363":"1363","1362":"1362","1308":"1308","Repton, Derbyshire, England":"Repton, Derbyshire, England","Kent, England":"Kent, England","Cheriton, Kent, England":"Cheriton, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Canterbury, Kent, England":"Canterbury, Kent, England"},"fi":{"1330–1377":"1330–1377","1346–Female":"1346–Kuollut","1363–1422":"1363–1422","1308–Male":"1308–Kuollut","1337":"1337","1346":"1346","1422":"1422","1377":"1377","1453":"1453","1330":"1330","1363":"1363","1362":"1362","1308":"1308","Repton, Derbyshire, England":"Repton, Derbyshire, England","Kent, England":"Kent, England","Cheriton, Kent, England":"Cheriton, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningask